# 🛍️ Retail Analytics Case Study (MySQL Workbench 8.0)

This project presents an **end-to-end Retail Analytics Case Study** built using **MySQL Workbench 8.0**, focusing on **data cleaning, customer segmentation, product performance analysis**, and **behavioral insights**.  
The goal is to help retail businesses **understand customer behavior**, **identify key revenue drivers**, and **support data-driven decision-making**.

---

## 📁 Project Files
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| File                                  | Description                                        |
|-------------------------------------- |----------------------------------------------------|
| 🧠 `retail_Analytics_case_study.sql` | Full SQL script (cleaning, analysis, segmentation) |
| 📘 `RETAIL ANALYTICS CASE STUDY.pdf` | Complete project report with queries & insights    |
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---

## 🧹 Data Cleaning
- Treated **NULL** and blank values  
- Removed **duplicates** using `ROW_NUMBER()` window function  
- Detected & handled **outliers** using **Tukey’s IQR** and **Z-Score**  
- Ensured referential integrity between tables  

---

## 📊 Analyses Performed

### 🔸 Product Performance
- Calculated **total sales** per product  
- Identified **Top 10%** and **Bottom 10%** performers for inventory & marketing  

### 🔸 Customer Segmentation
- **Demographic:** Age (0–18, 18–45, 45+)  
- **Geographic:** Based on `location`  
- **Gender-based:** Purchase distribution  

### 🔸 Customer Behavior
- **One-time Buyers** vs **Repeat Users**  
- **Active Customers:** ≥5 purchases in last 3 months  
- **Churn-Risk:** No purchase in last 90 days  
- **Premium/VIP Customers:** Top 10% by spend & frequency  

---

## 💡 Key Insights
- **95% repeat customers** → strong loyalty  
- **Top 10% products** drive majority revenue (Pareto Principle)  
- **Churn-risk segment** identified for reactivation  

---

## 📈 KPIs
- Average Order Value (AOV)  
- Average Quantity Purchased  
- Customer Retention & Churn Rate  

---

## 🧰 Tools & Concepts
**MySQL Workbench 8.0**, **SQL**, **CTEs**, **Window Functions**, **RFM Analysis**, **Data Cleaning**, **Outlier Detection**

